This is a hands on exercise 1 exploration.

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
pacman::p_load(tidyverse)
```
:::


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
exam_data <- read_csv("../data/Exam_data.csv")
```
:::

## Histogram of Exam Data
First, we compare exam data using a histogram

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
hist(exam_data$MATHS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

## ggplot objects

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


element into the plot

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

### geometric objects: 
geom_bar

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x=RACE)) +
  geom_bar()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

geom_dotplot

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_dotplot(dotsize = 0.5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

geom_histogram

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram()       
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-8-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

we can modify the geometric object by changing geom()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=20,            
                 color="black",      
                 fill="light blue")  
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-9-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

modify by changing aes()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, 
           fill = GENDER)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=20, 
                 color="grey30")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-10-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

geom_density()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_density()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-11-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

plotting 2 kernel density lines by using color

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x = MATHS, 
           colour = GENDER)) +
  geom_density()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-12-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

geom_boxplot

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS,       
           x= GENDER)) +    
  geom_boxplot()            
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-13-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

notched plot

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, 
           x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot(notch=TRUE)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-14-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

geom_violin()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, 
           x= GENDER)) +
  geom_violin()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-15-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

geom_point()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, 
           y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point()            
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-16-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

combination of geom objects

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, 
           x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot() +                    
  geom_point(position="jitter", 
             size = 0.5)        
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-17-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

## statistic function
### stat()
stat_summary()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  stat_summary(geom = "point",       
               fun = "mean",         
               colour ="red",        
               size=4)               
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-18-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

combine geom() and stat()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_point(stat="summary",        
             fun="mean",           
             colour="red",          
             size=4)          
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-19-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

how to add best fit curve on a scatterplot

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, 
           y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, 
              linewidth=0.5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-20-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

### facets
facet_wrap()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=20) +
    facet_wrap(~ CLASS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-21-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

facet_grid()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=20) +
    facet_grid(~ CLASS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-22-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

### coordinates
vertical coordinate

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x=RACE)) +
  geom_bar()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-23-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

using coord_flip()

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x=RACE)) +
  geom_bar() +
  coord_flip()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-24-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

changing the x and y axis range

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, size=0.5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-25-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, 
              size=0.5) +  
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(0,100),
                  ylim=c(0,100))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-26-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

### themes
bar chart using gray color

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x=RACE)) +
  geom_bar() +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_gray()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-27-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::

